public class PackageResource extends BaseReadableResource
A readable Resource in a package, as specified by PackagePath or ModuleResource (which has a ModuleReference and URI), and a name. Package resources can be constructed by several factory methods:
  • packageResource(ModuleResource)
  • packageResource(Listener listener, Class, String)
  • packageResource(Listener listener, PackagePath, String)
  • packageResource(PackagePath, FileName)
  • packageResource(PackagePath, FilePath)

They can also be retrieved from a (KivaKit) Package with these methods:

  • Package.resource(String)
  • ResourceFolder.resources()
  • Package.resources(Matcher)

Note that PackageResources cannot be retrieved from PackagePaths because package paths are used in *kivakit-core-kernel*, which cannot depend on *kivakit-core-resource*. The easiest way to get a resource from a package path is one of the factory methods above.

jonathanl (shibo)
